responses.text:
O God! Thou art my God alone;  
In silent awe, I bow before  
The power that shaped both flesh and stone,  
The love that calls my spirit more.  

No fleeting shadow claims my heart,  
Nor passing fancy fills my days;  
With Thee, true life and peace impart,  
My dawn begins in grateful praise.  

O God! My journey is Thine own;  
Thou art my hope, my God alone.
